   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Composting Latrines at the GGM Clinic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water and Sanitation are both necessary for health care delivery.  It is a simple fact.  You may treat the symptoms but if you don&apos;t take care of the underlying problem the condition will continue to repeat over and over.
The GGM clinic in Murray Town now has a newly installed well providing clean water but sanitation remains a problem.  New latrines are needed.  GGM is teaming up with a group of youths to introduce the concept of composting latrines for human waste.  Six latrines will be built</narrative>
  </description>
